 exclusion, violence, and domination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDemocracyzUnited States. 0aMonismxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aMonism. 0aPhilosophy, Americany19th century. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aethics, morality, morals, communication, liberal arts, connectivity, ralph waldo emerson, walt whitman, american literature, united states of america, usa, bhagavad gita, divinity, hierarchical, exclusion, domination, violence, philosophy, civilization, 19th century, transcendentalism, individualism, social criticism, poetry, humanist, realism, philosophical, goodness, self-reliant, independence, spirituality, hindu, scripture, hinduism, mahabharata, holy, krishna, arjuna, vishnu, moral dilemma.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226746166423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226746166/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles